                <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan> Funisulano <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Ani</abbr><ex>ensi</ex></expan> Vettoniano <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>uno</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>mil</abbr><ex>itum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> VI <expan><abbr>vict</abbr><ex>ricis</ex></expan> quaes<lb break="no" n="4"/>tori provinciae Siciliae <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>uno</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pleb</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>praet</abbr><ex>ori</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ato</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> IIII <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Scythic</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>praef</abbr><ex>ecto</ex></expan> aerari Satur<lb break="no" n="7"/>ni curatori viae Aemiliae co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>VIIvir</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan> epulonum <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ato</ex></expan> pro <expan><abbr>pr</abbr><ex>aetore</ex></expan> <lb n="9"/><expan><abbr>provinc</abbr><ex>iae</ex></expan> Delmatiae <note>sic</note> item pro<lb break="no" n="10"/><expan><abbr>vinc</abbr><ex>iae</ex></expan> Pannoniae item Moesiae <lb n="11"/>superioris donato <del rend="erasure">[ab</del>] <lb n="12"/><del rend="erasure">[<expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratore</ex></expan> Domitiano <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> Germani</del>]<lb break="no" n="13"/><del rend="erasure">[co</del>] bello Dacico coronis IIII <lb n="14"/>murali vallari classica aurea <lb n="15"/>hastis puris IIII vex&amp;lt;il&amp;gt;lis IIII <lb n="16"/>patrono <lb n="17"/><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecurionum</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">D(eae)</supplied> <expan><abbr>Nem</abbr><ex>esi</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Reg</abbr><ex>inae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>sac</abbr><ex>rum</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied> <expan><abbr>Iul</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Victorinus <expan><abbr>ve</abbr><ex>teranus</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">c(ivis)</supplied> <expan><abbr>mun</abbr><ex>icipii</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>And</abbr><ex>autoniensium</ex></expan> cum suis <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Inschriftträger: möglicherweise auch Mittelteil einer Statuenbasis; im 3. Jh. n. Chr wiederverwendet: auf der Rückseite Weihinschrift mit Reliefdarstellung der Nemesis (Buchstabenhöhe 3,5-2,5 cm). (B): Vorderseite: Fitz: Z. 8 (Anfang): vir; Rückseite: AIJ 474: Z. 1: D(eae); Selem: Z. 1: D(eae) Nem(esi) sac(rum); CIL 03, 04008; ILS 3746: Z. 2: vet(eranus). Datierung: nach dem Sieg Domitians über die Daker (86 n. Chr.) und vor dem Prokonsulat des Funisulanus Vettonianus in Africa (spätestens 91/92 n. Chr.).</p>
            </div>
